headline: US Plans Thousands of Shutdown Furloughs But Silent on Firings
summary: At least eight cabinet departments comprising more than two-thirds of the federal workforce had detailed their shutdown plans as of Monday afternoon.  The Centers for Disease Control and Prevention said it had 1,563 positions in “RIF status,” but it was unclear whether those reductions were previously authorized or part of the shutdown plan.  Officials at the CDC and the Department of Health and Human Services did not respond to requests for comment about the language in the CDC contingency plan.
